title: Blackhole
lyrics:
On your enigmatic horizon
The whole cosmos is projected
But beyond that...Yo!


Your mysteries remain undetected



My yearning to unravel you



Is as infinite as your depths



I can't help myself



(know what I'm saying)



I want to achieve an intercept



You're dangerous, you could swallow me whole



But I don't know if I want to escape



Maybe being part of you is my goal



(dope)



Maybe it's my signed and sealed fate



But still you tease me constantly



(yeh)



With your...inscrutability



(unh)



You rip my heart apart yet...



It's my sea...of tranquility





The quantum blocks of your gravity wall hide a microcosm, let's share our worlds...



Let's share it all! 



Oh my science, I wanna know will you join me in a Love Alliance,



A Love Alliance!





So many things I wanna say but I can't find the words



'Cos we're so far away, so far away! 



Round and round suitors waltz with you



In a banquet of drummond light



They don't know what awaits ahead



Because you shine so bright



Unaware of your void secrets



Eventually you'll devour them all



While you wait for aeons



(aha)



For one to come that will never fall



Come take my hand



(yeh)



We can exchange wonderful science about strange new lands



(fresh!)



Beautiful new...lands...





The quantum blocks of your gravity wall hide a microcosm, let's share our worlds...



Let's share it all! 



Oh my science, I wanna know will you join me in a Love Alliance,



A Love Alliance!





(sex panther noises)





(Yo, I'm gonna drop the science



Megalithic in the house 2018!



We're going to blow your fucking minds!



...with science!)





(scatting)





The quantum blocks of your gravity wall hide a microcosm, let's share our worlds...



Let's share it all! 



Oh my science, I wanna know will you join me in a Love Alliance,



A Love Alliance!





(more sex panther noises)
